### Fire one AI-service invocation. The first call triggers the bug:
### a WARN from DefaultAiServiceListenerRegistrar appears in the Quarkus log
### complaining about Prometheus tag-key mismatch on guardrail_invoked_total.
GET http://localhost:8080/chat?q=hi

### Second call — the legacy meter is already registered, so the WARN
### still appears (every event-based registration attempt still collides).
GET http://localhost:8080/chat?q=again

### Inspect the registered meters. Note that only the legacy schema
### ([class, method, result, exception]) survives — the richer
### event-based schema is silently dropped.
GET http://localhost:8080/q/metrics
Accept: text/plain

### Filter to just the guardrail meters.
GET http://localhost:8080/q/metrics
Accept: text/plain

> {%
client.log(response.body.split('\n').filter(l => l.includes('guardrail')).join('\n'));
%}